  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Providing access to quality education and psychosocial support to conflict-affected children in NW and SW regions of Cameroon</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims to rapidly improve access to inclusive and quality education for children in crisis-affected areas through three main key actions:

1. Support non-formal centres through the production and dissemination of pre-recorded lessons and internet-based online/offline learning modules

2. Capitation grants to confessional and private lay schools that are operating at a significantly reduced enrolment rate. 
3. Support to monitoring of school closures, affected schools, and attacks on education. UNESCO will support the establishment of a reporting mechanism for schools and will also set guidelines for local partners to monitor and produce independence reports.</narrative>
  </description>
